A woman in Somerset who is offering to help others learn basic plumbing skills says she is surprised by the response so far.  Debs van Meeuwen-Jones has set up a workshop from a garage in Fivehead.The retired plumber put a post on Nextdoor and Facebook in October.She has now received 55 enquiries and 26 women have signed up to the paid-for sessions.
One of the women in the workshop, Catherine said: "We had a leak in our home six months ago and I wanted to learn how to look after a house."Ms van Meeuwen-Jones, 62, says she wanted to "empower people" to help women gain confidence by teaching them skills such as replacing taps and washers.
